I visited this place
Israel35,877 contributions
Fantastic- just fantastic
Mar 2024 Solo
PROS
* The most spectacular viewing platform for the Eiffel Tower
* Very extremely popular wide massive spacious plaza
* Primary location for scenic and staged photo opportunities
* Interesting semi-circular buildings and many large sculptures adorn the outside
* Location of several museums, including marine and ethnology
* Easy access from metro station

CONS
* Crowded- always crowded
* It is a wide open space and can be windy
* Everyone wants their private solo portrait or selfie, and others are in the way
* Because of the crowds and the size and the distractions, this can be a prime target for stalkers, scammers and pickpockets

"I VISITED THIS PLACE"...
... as the first thing that I did and at dawn on the my first day in Paris after my nighttime arrival. I took the metro M1 from Le Marais area and transferred to M6 to get to Trocadero station. The plaza with the iconic view is across a busy street and past the little park with the statue of General Foch on a horse.

Coming face-to-face with the sheer gigantic size and splendor of the "iron lady" is breathtaking and spellbinding- one stands there in awe- it is even larger than one imagines. It's a truly tremendous moment.

I loved being there at dawn and I savored the moment. However, I wasn't alone; there were already tens of people on that platform, all looking for the perfect photo/selfie opportunity. I took many "helpful" photos of the Eiffel Tower, of anonymous people being photographed in front of it, the people photographing them, and also the Trocadero buildings and the statues also.

During my touristic wanderings and meanderings, I passed through this Trocadero plaza a good number of times- it was always extremely crowded with tourists and gawkers, and there were a lot of tour groups and traffic jams of double decker buses full of people with selfie sticks on the upper level and there were always hawkers selling their wares that they had placed out on a carpet on the street sidewalk.

WAS IT WORTH THE COST?
Yes- it is free

WOULD "I VISIT THIS PLACE" AGAIN?
For sure

ADVICE
* Be sure to go and get your photos
* Best time is early morning
*. Be aware of your surroundings
Written May 30, 2024

Excellent place for children and adults!
Dec 2022 Family
Le Trocadero et son esplanade are located in front of the Eiffel Tower, the most important tourist point in Pars. It is a place, always full of people, from where you can see the best views of Eiffel Tower and surroundings. So, it is a perfect green zone, where you can sit, relax and do a picnic, or come to play with children if you are on holidays in the city. Really, a fantastic place for children and adults. A very recommendable option to come before or after visiting Eiffel Tower, in the day or at night, always.
(See also Fontaine du Trocadero, Les Jardins du Trocadero and Eiffel Tower)

Views of Eiffel Tower and much more
Jul 2023 Family
Great area for walking and taking iconic photos of the Eiffel Tower. Rating this four stars vice five because of the riffraff you may encounter in the area. Avoid anyone asking you if you speak English or those asking for "donations". These are well trained pickpockets trying to distract you or extort you for money. Watch their hands at all times. A common tactic of late is to pretend to be taking photos of the Tower and then as you're taking photos too they snatch your bag right from the ground at your feet. Seen it happen. Just be careful and enjoy the views. Very touristy area, but worth visiting for photos.
Written September 6, 2023
